JOHANNESBURG - The DA says the ANC must come clean about its involvement in an alleged 'War Room' smear campaign.A secret organisation was allegedly set up to damage the image of opposition parties before last year s municipal elections.READ: ANC must own up after smear campaign tapes released: MaimaneIn a statement, DA leader Mmusi Maimane says it's hard to ignore mounting evidence against the governing party.Explosive audio recordings suggest ANC General Manager Ignatius Jacobs was aware of the 'War Room s' work, and discussed how it should be funded.The ANC has distanced itself from the campaign.eNCA